---
description: Vector store (Pinecone), embeddings, and similarity search for VidShield AI
globs: backend/app/ai/**, backend/app/services/*embed*, backend/app/services/*vector*, retrieval/**, embeddings/**
---

AI/vector stack (VidShield AI):
- OpenAI API for embeddings (e.g. frame or text embeddings).
- Pinecone for vector search (e.g. similarity search against known bad content, or metadata retrieval).
- Optional: RAG-style retrieval over policy docs or knowledge base for agent context.

Vector architecture:
- Separate embedding generation, indexing, retrieval, and consumption by agents/chains.
- Keep retrieval logic independent from moderation decision logic where possible.
- Preserve source metadata for traceability (video_id, frame timestamp, policy_id).

Rules:
- Never dump raw full documents or full video metadata into prompts when chunking/embedding is expected.
- Use deterministic embedding and indexing strategies unless explicitly experimenting.
- Maintain metadata: source, video_id, timestamp, tenant, policy context.
- Prefer configurable retrieval parameters: top_k, filters, score thresholds.
- Support similarity search for known violations or reference content; use in safety_checker or report_generator as needed.

Knowledge/reference data (if used):
- Support ingestion of reference content (e.g. known bad frames, policy snippets); normalize and sanitize; preserve version/identity.
- Ground moderation or reporting in retrieved context; handle no-context and low-confidence gracefully.

Do not:
- Mix ingestion code with runtime moderation/analysis in the same module.
- Make retrieval behavior impossible to inspect or tune.
- Hide retrieval failures silently.
